Docker Link:
docker pull splunk/splunk

docker run -d -e "SPLUNK_START_ARGS=--accept-license" -e "SPLUNK_USER=root" -p "8000:8000" splunk/splunk

Then visit http://127.0.0.1:8000


Check out Splunk App for Stream as well. Captures data off the wire. Just make your own streams vs using OOTB enabled ones.
https://github.com/Neo23x0/sigma

... | top helps you find what is common, but ... | rare will show you what doesn't belong
https://github.com/Neo23x0/sigma - Sigma is a generic and open signature format that allows you to describe relevant log events in a straight forward manner. 
Sigma is for log files what Snort is for network traffic and YARA is for files.

